            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine most of the <strong>grated cheese</strong> (save some for later!) with your <strong>cornflour</strong> in a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) and mix until the cheese is coated in the flour</p><p>Add 260ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[395ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[530ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>to the pan with 30ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [45ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [60ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Cook over a medium heat for 3-4 min, stirring frequently, or until the cheese has melted and the sauce has thickened – this is your <strong>cheese sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-15-1702989471322-x200.jpg",
